To get all loaded assemblies or referenced assemblies from a `ModuleDefinition` in Mono.Cecil, you can use the following properties:

To get all loaded assemblies:

```csharp
var loadedAssemblies = moduleDefinition.AssemblyResolver.GetAssemblies();
```

This will return an `AssemblyDefinition` collection containing all loaded assemblies.

To get all referenced assemblies:

```csharp
var referencedAssemblies = moduleDefinition.AssemblyReferences;
```

This will return an `AssemblyNameReference` collection containing all referenced assemblies.

If you want to load the referenced assemblies as `AssemblyDefinition` objects, you can use the `AssemblyResolver` to resolve them:

```csharp
var resolver = moduleDefinition.AssemblyResolver;
var referencedAssemblyDefinitions = new List<AssemblyDefinition>();

foreach (var reference in moduleDefinition.AssemblyReferences)
{
    var assembly = resolver.Resolve(reference);
    if (assembly != null)
    {
        referencedAssemblyDefinitions.Add(assembly);
    }
}
```

This code will create a list of `AssemblyDefinition` objects for all successfully resolved referenced assemblies.

Note that you may need to configure the `AssemblyResolver` to locate and load the referenced assemblies correctly, depending on your specific use case and the location of the assemblies.

