To provide a dynamic collection of assemblies, you can create a list or an array of assembly names or types, and then use LINQ to load the corresponding assemblies. Here's an example:

```csharp
public virtual IEnumerable<Assembly> RequiredAssemblies()
{
    // Define the list of assembly names or types you want to include
    var assemblyNames = new[]
    {
        "TeleCore.Loader",
        "MyAssembly1",
        "MyAssembly2",
        typeof(SomeTypeInAnotherAssembly).Assembly.FullName
    };

    // Use LINQ to load the assemblies
