}
```

In this example:

1. We create an array `assemblyNames` that contains the names of the assemblies we want to include. You can add or remove assembly names from this array as needed.
2. We use the `Select` LINQ method to load each assembly by calling `Assembly.Load` with the assembly name or full name.
3. The `ToList` method is used to materialize the result as a list, which implements `IEnumerable<Assembly>`.

