The workaround involves using the `Compilation` property of the `GeneratorExecutionContext` object, which is passed to the `Execute` method of your `ISourceGenerator` implementation. Here's how you can do it:

```csharp
using Microsoft.CodeAnalysis;

[Generator]
public class MySourceGenerator : ISourceGenerator
{
    public void Initialize(GeneratorInitializationContext context)
    {
        // No initialization required for this example
    }

    public void Execute(GeneratorExecutionContext context)
    {
        // Get the output directory from the Compilation object
        string outputDirectory = GetOutputDirectory(context.Compilation);

        // Create the file path
        string filePath = Path.Combine(outputDirectory, "metadata.txt");

        // Generate the content for the file
        string fileContent = "This is the metadata content.";

        // Create the file in the output directory
        File.WriteAllText(filePath, fileContent);
    }

    private static string GetOutputDirectory(Compilation compilation)
    {
        // Get the output path from the Compilation object
        string outputPath = compilation.Options.OutputPath;

        // If the output path is not set, use the current directory
        if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(outputPath))
        {
            outputPath = Directory.GetCurrentDirectory();
        }

        // Return the output directory
        return Path.GetDirectoryName(outputPath);
    }
}
```

Here's what's happening in the code above:

