However, there is a workaround that you can use to achieve the desired behavior of copying the generated file to the output directory. Instead of trying to set the file metadata directly, you can leverage the project's build system and the `AdditionalFiles` item in the project file.

Here's how you can do it:

1. In your `ISourceGenerator` implementation, generate the file content and write it to a temporary file in the project's directory.

```csharp
using Microsoft.CodeAnalysis;
using Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.Text;

[Generator]
public class MySourceGenerator : ISourceGenerator
{
